  "doc": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Function calling (also called tool use) lets an LLM emit a structured request to invoke a function rather than generating free-form text. The model doesn't execute code — it outputs a JSON object naming the function and its arguments. Your application executes the function, appends the result to the conversation, and sends everything back to the model, which incorporates the result into its next response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Function calling loop: user request → LLM emits tool_calls JSON → app executes tool → tool result appended → re-sent to LLM → final answer; parallel tool calls and tool_choice modes"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Defining Tools"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each tool is described with a JSON Schema object specifying its name, a description the model uses to decide when to call it, and the schema for its parameters. The description quality matters: a vague description leads to incorrect tool selection."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "tools = [\n    {\n        \"type\": \"function\",\n        \"function\": {\n            \"name\": \"get_weather\",\n            \"description\": (\n                \"Retrieve the current weather conditions for a city. \"\n                \"Use when the user asks about weather, temperature, or forecast.\"\n            ),\n            \"parameters\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                    \"location\": {\n                        \"type\": \"string\",\n                        \"description\": \"City name, optionally with country (e.g. 'Paris, FR').\",\n                    },\n                    \"units\": {\n                        \"type\": \"string\",\n                        \"enum\": [\"celsius\", \"fahrenheit\"],\n                        \"description\": \"Temperature unit. Defaults to celsius.\",\n                    },\n                },\n                \"required\": [\"location\"],\n            },\n        },\n    },\n    {\n        \"type\": \"function\",\n        \"function\": {\n            \"name\": \"search_web\",\n            \"description\": (\n                \"Search the web for current information. Use for facts, news, \"\n                \"or any topic that may have changed since the model's training cutoff.\"\n            ),\n            \"parameters\": {\n                \"type\": \"object\",\n                \"properties\": {\n                    \"query\": {\"type\": \"string\", \"description\": \"Search query string.\"},\n                    \"num_results\": {\"type\": \"integer\", \"description\": \"Number of results (1–10).\"},\n                },\n                \"required\": [\"query\"],\n            },\n        },\n    },\n]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Single Tool Call Loop (OpenAI API)"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import json\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\nclient = OpenAI()\n\n\ndef get_weather(location: str, units: str = \"celsius\") -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Real implementation would call a weather API.\"\"\"\n    return {\"location\": location, \"temp\": 14, \"condition\": \"partly cloudy\", \"units\": units}\n\n\nTOOL_FUNCTIONS = {\"get_weather\": get_weather}\n\n\ndef run_conversation(user_message: str) -> str:\n    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}]\n\n    while True:\n        response = client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n            messages=messages,\n            tools=tools,\n            tool_choice=\"auto\",\n        )\n        msg = response.choices[0].message\n        messages.append(msg)  # always append the assistant turn\n\n        if response.choices[0].finish_reason == \"tool_calls\":\n            for tc in msg.tool_calls:\n                fn = TOOL_FUNCTIONS[tc.function.name]\n                args = json.loads(tc.function.arguments)\n                result = fn(**args)\n                messages.append({\n                    \"role\": \"tool\",\n                    \"tool_call_id\": tc.id,\n                    \"content\": json.dumps(result),\n                })\n        else:\n            # finish_reason == \"stop\" → final text answer\n            return msg.content\n\n\nprint(run_conversation(\"What's the weather like in Tokyo right now?\"))"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Parallel Tool Calls"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When the model needs multiple pieces of information simultaneously, it can emit several tool calls in a single response. Execute them concurrently and append all results before the next API call."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nimport json\nfrom openai import AsyncOpenAI\n\nclient = AsyncOpenAI()\n\n\nasync def get_weather_async(location: str, units: str = \"celsius\") -> dict:\n    await asyncio.sleep(0.1)  # simulate network\n    return {\"location\": location, \"temp\": 14, \"condition\": \"cloudy\"}\n\n\nASYNC_TOOLS = {\"get_weather\": get_weather_async}\n\n\nasync def run_parallel_conversation(user_message: str) -> str:\n    messages = [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message}]\n\n    while True:\n        response = await client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o-mini\",\n            messages=messages,\n            tools=tools,\n            tool_choice=\"auto\",\n        )\n        msg = response.choices[0].message\n        messages.append(msg)\n\n        if response.choices[0].finish_reason == \"tool_calls\":\n            # Execute all tool calls concurrently\n            async def execute(tc):\n                fn = ASYNC_TOOLS[tc.function.name]\n                args = json.loads(tc.function.arguments)\n                result = await fn(**args)\n                return {\n                    \"role\": \"tool\",\n                    \"tool_call_id\": tc.id,\n                    \"content\": json.dumps(result),\n                }\n\n            tool_results = await asyncio.gather(*[execute(tc) for tc in msg.tool_calls])\n            messages.extend(tool_results)\n        else:\n            return msg.content\n\n\n# \"What's the weather in London and Paris?\" → model calls get_weather twice in parallel\nresult = asyncio.run(run_parallel_conversation(\"Compare the weather in London and Paris.\"))\nprint(result)"
          }
        ]
      },
